{
  "texts": [
    "Data points that were incorrectly predicted by the previous models are given higher weight, while those accurately predicted have their weight reduced.",
    "As the iterations continue, challenging examples receive increasing attention.",
    "After N iterations, each of the N weak learners is assigned a model weight (w) to contribute to the final model 66, 70.",
    "The boosting procedure is shown in Fig. 6, wherein AdaBoost increases the weight of training data that the prior model underfits.",
    "The weighted sum of this combination is the result of the AdaBoost model."
  ]
}